1
00:00:01,635 --> 00:00:05,139
( Cameo laughs )

2
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:07,408
I’m sure it’s quite
the traumatic experience

3
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:10,544
being eaten alive
by your own sister.

4
00:00:10,577 --> 00:00:14,014
Then again, when a man
uncovers his deepest desires,

5
00:00:14,047 --> 00:00:16,349
all of his weaknesses
are laid bare.

6
00:00:16,383 --> 00:00:19,052
You gave nary a thought
to the depraved nature

7
00:00:19,086 --> 00:00:22,456
of bringing someone
back to the world of the living.

8
00:00:22,489 --> 00:00:24,257
Everyone desperately
wants to believe

9
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:27,694
that their loved ones
are still alive somewhere.

10
00:00:27,728 --> 00:00:30,431
More than anything else,
your hope is that,

11
00:00:30,464 --> 00:00:33,167
by some miracle,
they’ll suddenly pop in tomorrow

12
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,568
and say, "good morning."

13
00:00:35,602 --> 00:00:37,304
Oh, before I forget,

14
00:00:37,337 --> 00:00:40,173
I believe you said something
about a third wish,

15
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:43,277
but, if i’m not mistaken,
you’ve already made said wish.

16
00:00:43,310 --> 00:00:45,546
( Polnareff gasps ) You mean...

17
00:00:45,579 --> 00:00:49,249
Cameo: You wished for avdol
to come back to life!

18
00:00:49,283 --> 00:00:51,452
Hail 2 u!

19
00:00:57,624 --> 00:00:59,659
( Wind blowing )

20
00:01:12,339 --> 00:01:13,841
( Polnareff gasps )

21
00:01:13,874 --> 00:01:16,410
♪

22
00:01:16,443 --> 00:01:18,445
No. He’s...

23
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:22,149
( Avdol roars )

24
00:01:22,182 --> 00:01:24,851
( Polnareff screams )

25
00:01:24,885 --> 00:01:26,887
♪

26
00:01:34,228 --> 00:01:36,230
( Singing in Japanese )

27
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:13,400
( Polnareff screams )

28
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:15,535
- Avdol, it’s me!
- ( Avdol screams )

29
00:02:18,372 --> 00:02:19,640
( Polnareff gasping )

30
00:02:19,673 --> 00:02:21,742
Av-avdol, why?

31
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:26,580
Avdol: My fingers,
they’ve crumbled to pieces.

32
00:02:26,613 --> 00:02:27,814
( Groans )

33
00:02:27,848 --> 00:02:30,851
On your feet, polnareff!

34
00:02:30,884 --> 00:02:32,853
I blame you for all of this.

35
00:02:32,886 --> 00:02:35,622
Because of
your idiotic bumbling, i--

36
00:02:35,656 --> 00:02:40,594
polnareff, because of you,
I ended up like this!

37
00:02:40,627 --> 00:02:42,729
♪

38
00:02:43,897 --> 00:02:47,401
Polnareff: Avdol, you’re right.

39
00:02:47,434 --> 00:02:48,702
The person to blame for this...

40
00:02:48,735 --> 00:02:50,904
Is me!

41
00:02:50,938 --> 00:02:54,308
Avdol: Mark my words.
You’ll pay for this, polnareff,

42
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:57,778
and you’ll do it
with your flesh!

43
00:02:57,811 --> 00:03:00,580
Sherry: I’ll get better
if I eat, right?

44
00:03:00,614 --> 00:03:04,284
Well, am I right?
Huh, big brother?!

45
00:03:04,318 --> 00:03:06,420
- ( Yells )
- ( Polnareff screams )

46
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:17,631
( Whimpering )

47
00:03:17,664 --> 00:03:20,934
Sherry:
What’s the matter, brother?

48
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:29,743
Polnareff: S-stay away!
Stay away from me!

49
00:03:29,776 --> 00:03:30,744
Both of you!

50
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:33,880
Please go back to your graves!

51
00:03:33,914 --> 00:03:38,585
Sherry: But why? You’re the one
who brought us back, aren’t you?

52
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:41,789
Avdol: The time has come
for you to enter your grave!

53
00:03:41,822 --> 00:03:44,725
( Polnareff gasping )

54
00:03:44,758 --> 00:03:48,795
I-i’m so panicked
that I forgot to summon chariot.

55
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:52,299
How could I have been
so caught up in my wish

56
00:03:52,332 --> 00:03:54,634
that I neglected
to use my stand?

57
00:03:54,668 --> 00:03:56,870
( Gasps ) Leave me alone!

58
00:03:56,904 --> 00:03:58,706
Get away from me!

59
00:03:58,739 --> 00:04:00,941
Please, just stay away!

60
00:04:04,378 --> 00:04:05,813
What the--

61
00:04:05,846 --> 00:04:07,881
cameo: "Please"? Oh, no, no, no!

62
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:11,352
You don’t have
any wishes left, remember?!

63
00:04:11,385 --> 00:04:13,020
- ( Both growl )
- ( Polnareff screaming )

64
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:17,958
Cameo: I’ve already granted
your three wishes.

65
00:04:17,991 --> 00:04:19,559
( Laughs )

66
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:22,963
And i’m sorry to say
you don’t get any more!

67
00:04:24,531 --> 00:04:26,566
Polnareff: Stop it! Get off!

68
00:04:31,371 --> 00:04:34,574
Cameo: Hail 2 u!

69
00:04:34,608 --> 00:04:36,610
( Laughs )

70
00:04:36,643 --> 00:04:40,947
Go ahead. Writhe and scream to
your pathetic heart’s content.

71
00:04:40,981 --> 00:04:42,583
Since you’re
in the middle of nowhere,

72
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,918
your friends by the shore
won’t hear you.

73
00:04:44,952 --> 00:04:47,087
No one can save you now!

74
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,688
( Laughs )

75
00:04:52,726 --> 00:04:53,727
( Creatures chewing )

76
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,995
Polnareff: It’s no use.

77
00:04:55,028 --> 00:04:57,831
This is the end.

78
00:04:57,865 --> 00:05:01,035
I’m going to die. I’m finished.

79
00:05:01,068 --> 00:05:05,639
Sherry, avdol...

80
00:05:05,672 --> 00:05:10,043
I suppose you’re
giving me what I deserved.

81
00:05:10,077 --> 00:05:11,979
It’s only fitting.

82
00:05:12,012 --> 00:05:13,614
It’s like you said.

83
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:16,016
You died
because of my actions...

84
00:05:17,351 --> 00:05:19,520
♪

85
00:05:19,553 --> 00:05:22,089
( Sobs )

86
00:05:22,122 --> 00:05:25,692
And so i’ve accepted my fate.

87
00:05:27,895 --> 00:05:28,896
( Gasps )

88
00:05:30,931 --> 00:05:32,499
Huh?

89
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:34,635
♪

90
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:38,038
What? My vision must be going.

91
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:39,773
I’m seeing double.

92
00:05:39,806 --> 00:05:43,109
It looks like
there are two avdols.

93
00:05:43,143 --> 00:05:44,511
Huh?

94
00:05:44,545 --> 00:05:45,713
( Chuckles )

95
00:05:45,746 --> 00:05:48,716
Of course
there’s not another one.

96
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:51,652
If i’m starting to see things,

97
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:53,854
guess it means the end is near.

98
00:05:53,887 --> 00:05:57,057
The blood loss
is taking its toll.

99
00:05:57,090 --> 00:05:59,159
I’m hallucinating.

100
00:05:59,193 --> 00:06:02,930
All right, this is it.

101
00:06:02,963 --> 00:06:04,898
I’ll have to tap out early.

102
00:06:04,932 --> 00:06:09,570
Goodbye, Mr. Joestar,
kakyoin, jotaro.

103
00:06:09,603 --> 00:06:11,972
I pray for your victory.

104
00:06:12,005 --> 00:06:14,407
As for you, avdol,

105
00:06:14,441 --> 00:06:17,744
i’ll atone in the next world.

106
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,982
- Hmm?
- ( Double groaning )

107
00:06:24,117 --> 00:06:25,118
( Avdol chuckles )

108
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:29,689
Cameo: What? Impossible!

109
00:06:29,723 --> 00:06:31,725
Polnareff: Huh? I was right!

110
00:06:31,758 --> 00:06:33,660
I just knew I saw another avdol!

111
00:06:33,694 --> 00:06:35,563
My eyes weren’t playing tricks!

112
00:06:35,596 --> 00:06:38,099
Besides the dirt
and dust version cameo made,

113
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:39,933
there’s another avdol!

114
00:06:41,435 --> 00:06:43,904
Avdol: Magician’s red!

115
00:06:43,937 --> 00:06:45,939
( Magician’s red squawks )

116
00:06:46,974 --> 00:06:50,644
( Double screams )

117
00:06:52,946 --> 00:06:55,115
Cameo: But how?!
He’s supposed to be dead!

118
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:59,452
It’s impossible! He was stabbed
by the hanged man, centerfold!

119
00:06:59,486 --> 00:07:01,722
Polnareff:
How the hell is he alive?!

120
00:07:07,628 --> 00:07:09,063
Avdol: Tsk, tsk.

121
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:10,798
Polnareff: Are you
really Mohammed avdol?!

122
00:07:10,831 --> 00:07:14,101
Avdol: Yes, you had
better believe I am!

123
00:07:14,134 --> 00:07:16,637
♪

124
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:18,972
Polnareff: Is it really you?

125
00:07:19,006 --> 00:07:20,741
Avdol: Tsk, tsk.

126
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:22,476
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

127
00:07:24,478 --> 00:07:26,981
Polnareff: I-is it
the real you, I mean?

128
00:07:27,014 --> 00:07:30,751
Avdol: Polnareff, you haven’t
changed in the slightest.

129
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:34,221
You still lose all common sense
when it comes to your sister

130
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:36,623
and never stop to think
of the consequences.

131
00:07:36,657 --> 00:07:39,560
Cameo: I simply refuse
to accept this!

132
00:07:39,593 --> 00:07:41,161
Mohammad avdol is dead!

133
00:07:41,195 --> 00:07:43,898
I was told hol horse
put a bullet between your eyes

134
00:07:43,931 --> 00:07:46,066
after hanged man
sunk his blade into your back

135
00:07:46,099 --> 00:07:48,101
- and you died on the spot!
- ( Avdol chuckles )

136
00:07:48,135 --> 00:07:50,971
You’re correct
about me being shot,

137
00:07:51,004 --> 00:07:53,073
right in the forehead.

138
00:07:53,106 --> 00:07:56,242
That said, because I was
stabbed in the back,

139
00:07:56,276 --> 00:07:58,812
for a moment,
my face was looking up,

140
00:07:58,846 --> 00:08:01,949
and the bullet only grazed me.

141
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:05,886
I suppose this is what one would
call a blessing in disguise.

142
00:08:05,919 --> 00:08:07,220
Hol horse didn’t realize it,

143
00:08:07,254 --> 00:08:09,723
but his bullet never
made contact with my brain,

144
00:08:09,756 --> 00:08:11,691
so he didn’t inflict
a mortal wound.

145
00:08:11,725 --> 00:08:15,963
He was only able to scratch
my skin and bruise my skull.

146
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:17,564
( Cameo growls )

147
00:08:17,598 --> 00:08:20,000
Avdol: Although I did
completely lose consciousness.

148
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:22,202
( Cameo growls )

149
00:08:22,236 --> 00:08:25,940
Avdol: So you call yourself
cameo of the judgment card.

150
00:08:25,973 --> 00:08:28,909
Hell is near, so prepare...

151
00:08:28,942 --> 00:08:31,645
For hell 2 u!

152
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:35,282
♪

153
00:08:35,315 --> 00:08:39,820
Polnareff: I know it was only
the third wish, but still...

154
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:43,090
It’s really him.

155
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:45,192
It came true!

156
00:08:49,429 --> 00:08:52,465
Avdol: Mohammed avdol
is indeed alive and well.

157
00:08:52,499 --> 00:08:54,768
I would call this bad news.

158
00:08:54,801 --> 00:08:57,437
That being the case,
shouldn’t you scurry away

159
00:08:57,471 --> 00:09:00,374
to inform dio and your
fellow stand user compatriots

160
00:09:00,407 --> 00:09:01,441
about my return?

161
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:03,377
( Cameo growls )

162
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:05,913
Avdol: Well,
shouldn’t you, cameo?

163
00:09:05,946 --> 00:09:06,914
( Cameo groans )

164
00:09:06,947 --> 00:09:08,415
Polnareff: That’s right!

165
00:09:08,448 --> 00:09:09,649
I have to tell them!

166
00:09:09,683 --> 00:09:11,952
I have to let
Mr. Joestar, kakyoin,

167
00:09:11,985 --> 00:09:14,588
and jotaro know!
Avdol’s back!

168
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:17,624
Cameo: This is very
surprising news, to be sure,

169
00:09:17,658 --> 00:09:21,395
but the way I see it,
I can spin it this way.

170
00:09:21,428 --> 00:09:24,464
Not only did judgment’s cameo
slay the idiot polnareff,

171
00:09:24,498 --> 00:09:27,434
but also succeeded
in eliminating avdol,

172
00:09:27,467 --> 00:09:29,636
who was actually alive!

173
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:33,874
Oh, I can’t wait
to tell them the splendid news!

174
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:35,609
Avdol: Magician’s red!

175
00:09:38,412 --> 00:09:39,880
Cameo: Whoa, there.

176
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:40,914
( Laughs )

177
00:09:44,885 --> 00:09:46,387
( Avdol groans )

178
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:47,554
Polnareff: Avdol!

179
00:09:47,588 --> 00:09:48,656
( Groans )

180
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:50,925
Avdol: This stand...

181
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:52,827
It’s far more powerful
than I expected.

182
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:56,063
Polnareff: Be careful.
It’s not just his power.

183
00:09:56,096 --> 00:09:58,332
This guy’s got
incredible speed, too.

184
00:09:58,365 --> 00:10:02,669
Cameo: Come now, avdol. Is that
the extent of your abilities?

185
00:10:02,703 --> 00:10:05,339
If so, then sharing my good news

186
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:07,407
will be even easier
than expected.

187
00:10:08,542 --> 00:10:10,811
May fortune...

188
00:10:10,844 --> 00:10:11,912
- ( Sherry gasps )
- ( Polnareff gasps )

189
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:14,014
Cameo: Be with you both!

190
00:10:18,018 --> 00:10:19,052
Avdol: What now?!

191
00:10:19,086 --> 00:10:21,589
Cameo: Hail 2 u!

192
00:10:29,596 --> 00:10:31,565
Sherry: Big brother...

193
00:10:31,598 --> 00:10:33,066
Polnareff:
No, stop this charade.

194
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,969
You’re not the real Sherry.

195
00:10:35,002 --> 00:10:38,138
My Sherry is gone, dead!

196
00:10:38,172 --> 00:10:41,442
- ( Sobs )
- ( Chorus vocalizing )

197
00:10:41,475 --> 00:10:45,713
You’re nothing but...

198
00:10:46,847 --> 00:10:48,215
A hunk of dirt!

199
00:10:48,248 --> 00:10:50,217
( Sherry gasps )

200
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,154
But, brother...

201
00:11:00,961 --> 00:11:02,062
Avdol: Polnareff.

202
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:04,431
Apologies.
I would like to take back

203
00:11:04,464 --> 00:11:06,700
what I said
about you not changing.

204
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:09,869
Polnareff: No, you were
right about me all along.

205
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:12,539
I’m the one
who should apologize.

206
00:11:15,075 --> 00:11:16,877
( Cameo laughs )

207
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,078
( Avdol and polnareff yell )

208
00:11:20,113 --> 00:11:21,781
( Cameo laughs )

209
00:11:21,815 --> 00:11:24,951
This battle
has already been decided.

210
00:11:24,985 --> 00:11:27,688
( Both groaning )

211
00:11:27,721 --> 00:11:29,623
Cameo: Tell you what, avdol.

212
00:11:29,656 --> 00:11:32,659
Before you head off
for that magic lamp in the sky,

213
00:11:32,693 --> 00:11:34,962
i’d like to hear
your three wishes.

214
00:11:34,995 --> 00:11:39,032
I’ll Grant them before I
put you to rest for good.

215
00:11:39,066 --> 00:11:42,169
Go ahead.
You may as well give it a shot.

216
00:11:42,202 --> 00:11:44,905
As I said,
you get three wishes.

217
00:11:44,938 --> 00:11:47,841
Polnareff: Quel salaud.
He’s making fools of us!

218
00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:49,210
Just ignore him, avdol.

219
00:11:49,243 --> 00:11:51,579
You don’t have to make
any wishes!

220
00:11:51,612 --> 00:11:52,813
( Avdol grunts )

221
00:11:52,846 --> 00:11:54,915
Polnareff: Avdol,
are you listening to me?

222
00:11:54,948 --> 00:11:57,884
( Avdol scoffs ) No good.

223
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,756
I want four wishes!

224
00:12:02,789 --> 00:12:03,757
Polnareff: Huh?!

225
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:05,525
Cameo: What?

226
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:07,761
Avdol: My wishes.
Can’t you hear?

227
00:12:07,794 --> 00:12:09,896
I’m asking you
to Grant my wishes,

228
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:12,232
only I want four
instead of three.

229
00:12:12,266 --> 00:12:14,034
( Cameo growls )

230
00:12:14,067 --> 00:12:15,635
Avdol: Tsk, tsk.

231
00:12:15,669 --> 00:12:18,906
Cameo: Avdol,
you can’t be serious.

232
00:12:18,939 --> 00:12:20,741
Avdol: Are you denying my wish?!

233
00:12:20,774 --> 00:12:23,210
Cameo, you’re the one
who offered to Grant them!

234
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:26,046
I’m going to make sure
you keep your promise!

235
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:30,250
Cameo: You still insist upon
this futile contest of power?

236
00:12:30,284 --> 00:12:31,285
( Laughs )

237
00:12:31,318 --> 00:12:33,053
Your kicks are nothing!

238
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:37,724
( Gasps ) What?!

239
00:12:37,758 --> 00:12:40,728
( Wails )

240
00:12:40,761 --> 00:12:42,730
Polnareff:
That’s the way! Super!

241
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:44,565
( Avdol scoffs )

242
00:12:44,598 --> 00:12:46,600
Tsk, tsk.

243
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:48,869
You should probably know
that my first wish

244
00:12:48,902 --> 00:12:50,771
was to make you
cry out in agony,

245
00:12:50,804 --> 00:12:53,073
and it came true.

246
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:54,941
Cameo: This is madness.

247
00:12:54,975 --> 00:12:57,878
How can you be
so much stronger than before?

248
00:12:57,911 --> 00:12:59,679
Avdol: The wound left behind

249
00:12:59,713 --> 00:13:01,181
after I was stabbed
by the hanged man

250
00:13:01,215 --> 00:13:03,117
hasn’t completely healed yet.

251
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,752
Because I was so focused

252
00:13:04,785 --> 00:13:06,787
on guarding my wound
from an assault,

253
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,789
I had to hold myself back
a little.

254
00:13:08,822 --> 00:13:09,890
Cameo: What?

255
00:13:09,923 --> 00:13:11,758
Avdol: It was
only three days ago

256
00:13:11,792 --> 00:13:13,994
that I was finally able
to stand again.

257
00:13:14,027 --> 00:13:16,196
But since I took a plane here
from India,

258
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:18,199
the trip was very easy.

259
00:13:18,232 --> 00:13:20,935
Polnareff: That’s avdol,
still the best.

260
00:13:20,968 --> 00:13:23,671
Avdol: And now
for my second wish!

261
00:13:25,239 --> 00:13:27,641
( Cameo gagging )

262
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:29,042
( Screams )

263
00:13:29,076 --> 00:13:31,779
Avdol: I wish for you
to scream out in utter terror.

264
00:13:31,812 --> 00:13:33,914
And while you’re at it,
Grant my third wish!

265
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:36,116
Cry in regret!

266
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:39,719
( Cameo wails )

267
00:13:41,688 --> 00:13:43,823
- ( Avdol growls )
- Polnareff: That bastard!

268
00:13:43,857 --> 00:13:44,925
He’s running away!

269
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:47,627
Wait, damn it! Get back here!

270
00:13:47,661 --> 00:13:51,064
Avdol: Shh. Polnareff, quiet.

271
00:13:51,098 --> 00:13:53,267
♪

272
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,602
With that kind
of power and speed,

273
00:13:55,636 --> 00:13:58,772
given the rule of stands,
the user must be hiding

274
00:13:58,805 --> 00:14:01,074
somewhere nearby,
supplying his stand with energy.

275
00:14:03,177 --> 00:14:05,613
( Polnareff grunts )

276
00:14:07,147 --> 00:14:09,149
Is he here?

277
00:14:09,183 --> 00:14:12,953
Avdol: Yes, he should be
hiding out very close to us.

278
00:14:18,659 --> 00:14:20,828
( Polnareff gasps )
Hey, could that be--

279
00:14:20,861 --> 00:14:22,796
avdol: Shh.

280
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:35,108
( Man wheezes )

281
00:14:35,142 --> 00:14:36,744
( Coughs )

282
00:14:36,777 --> 00:14:38,912
Avdol: Shh.

283
00:14:44,117 --> 00:14:46,720
( Man gasps )

284
00:14:46,753 --> 00:14:50,156
Polnareff: Has this user really
resorted to hiding underground?

285
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:51,758
Damn coward.

286
00:14:51,792 --> 00:14:55,029
How dare you use my sister
like some pawn in a game?

287
00:14:55,062 --> 00:14:57,831
For what you’ve done,
I think i’ll show you hell.

288
00:14:57,865 --> 00:14:59,367
Hell 2 u.

289
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,768
Connard.

290
00:15:01,802 --> 00:15:04,705
( Chuckles )

291
00:15:04,738 --> 00:15:08,141
I can think of a few things
to drop down this tube,

292
00:15:08,175 --> 00:15:10,310
like dirt and sand...

293
00:15:10,344 --> 00:15:12,713
A spider...

294
00:15:12,746 --> 00:15:14,982
- Ants, too...
- ( Avdol gasps )

295
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:18,118
Polnareff: And a match.

296
00:15:18,151 --> 00:15:20,954
♪

297
00:15:20,988 --> 00:15:21,956
( Man gasping )

298
00:15:21,989 --> 00:15:23,257
( Sputters )

299
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:25,425
Polnareff: Bastard.
I hope you’re ready,

300
00:15:25,459 --> 00:15:27,861
because your suffering
has barely begun.

301
00:15:27,895 --> 00:15:29,363
Avdol: Hey, polnareff.

302
00:15:29,396 --> 00:15:33,267
I do believe it’s time
for me to drain the snake.

303
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,268
Polnareff: Huh?

304
00:15:34,301 --> 00:15:36,003
Avdol: How about it, my friend?

305
00:15:36,036 --> 00:15:38,972
Shall we engage in the timeless
ritual of male bonding?

306
00:15:39,006 --> 00:15:41,475
Hmm. Tsk, tsk.

307
00:15:41,508 --> 00:15:42,943
Polnareff: Huh?

308
00:15:42,976 --> 00:15:44,077
Oh.

309
00:15:44,111 --> 00:15:45,079
( Yelps )

310
00:15:45,112 --> 00:15:46,380
( Man sighs )

311
00:15:46,413 --> 00:15:50,150
Somehow I made it
out of that mess alive.

312
00:15:50,184 --> 00:15:52,086
( Zipper unzips )

313
00:15:52,119 --> 00:15:54,755
Huh?

314
00:15:54,788 --> 00:15:55,822
( Gurgling )

315
00:15:55,856 --> 00:15:57,324
Avdol: Come on, polnareff.

316
00:15:57,357 --> 00:15:59,226
- Let me hear you laugh!
- Polnareff: Uh...

317
00:15:59,259 --> 00:16:00,427
Avdol: I want to hear

318
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,729
the heartiest laugh
that you can muster!

319
00:16:02,763 --> 00:16:04,832
( Laughs )

320
00:16:04,865 --> 00:16:07,234
Polnareff: Avdol,
I might be wrong about this,

321
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:10,070
but it seems like you’re
the one who’s changed.

322
00:16:10,103 --> 00:16:11,905
Before the incident,
you would have never thought

323
00:16:11,939 --> 00:16:13,441
of doing something
quite so perverse.

324
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:15,709
( Chuckles ) This--

325
00:16:15,742 --> 00:16:18,845
this isn’t a result of you
being shot in the head, is it?

326
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:20,848
( Avdol laughing )

327
00:16:20,881 --> 00:16:22,883
( Polnareff laughing )

328
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:26,386
Avdol: That’s it!
Aim that thing!

329
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:27,721
Polnareff: Right!

330
00:16:27,754 --> 00:16:30,257
( Both laughing )

331
00:16:30,290 --> 00:16:33,093
( Man gagging )

332
00:16:33,126 --> 00:16:35,228
Huh? What the--

333
00:16:35,262 --> 00:16:37,898
( whimpering )

334
00:16:37,931 --> 00:16:40,300
Please I beg you, forgive me!

335
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:43,003
- Huh?
- Avdol: Last, but not least,

336
00:16:43,036 --> 00:16:46,106
my fourth wish
is to not Grant you

337
00:16:46,139 --> 00:16:49,009
a single one
of your pitiful wishes.

338
00:16:49,042 --> 00:16:53,446
My magician’s red forgives
no one, especially not you.

339
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,015
( Man gasps )

340
00:16:55,048 --> 00:16:56,483
( Groans )

341
00:16:59,253 --> 00:17:00,988
Polnareff: Ba-dum-tss!

342
00:17:01,355 --> 00:17:03,858
Polnareff: Hey!
You guys’ll never believe it!

343
00:17:03,891 --> 00:17:06,026
Guess who I ran into
while out and about?!

344
00:17:06,059 --> 00:17:08,061
Joseph: Polnareff,
we were worried about you.

345
00:17:08,095 --> 00:17:10,097
Kakyoin: Where did
those injuries come from?

346
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:11,765
Jotaro: Some kind of enemy?

347
00:17:11,798 --> 00:17:14,234
Polnareff: My wounds are nothing
compared to my news!

348
00:17:14,268 --> 00:17:16,904
Now listen up, and don’t
be too shocked, jotaro!

349
00:17:16,937 --> 00:17:18,672
And you’re gonna have to promise

350
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:20,840
you won’t throw your back out
in surprise, kakyoin.

351
00:17:20,874 --> 00:17:23,877
Who do you think I met
out there, Mr. Joestar?

352
00:17:23,911 --> 00:17:25,012
- Joseph: Huh?
- ( Polnareff giggles )

353
00:17:25,045 --> 00:17:27,581
Now prepare to be blown away!

354
00:17:27,614 --> 00:17:30,150
Tum-ta-da-da!

355
00:17:30,184 --> 00:17:32,887
Here he is!

356
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:36,924
That sly bastard avdol was
still alive! Isn’t that great?!

357
00:17:36,957 --> 00:17:39,660
( Hums fanfare )

358
00:17:39,693 --> 00:17:42,896
Joseph: Well, we should
probably get going.

359
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:45,933
Avdol: Here. Allow me
to help you carry your luggage.

360
00:17:45,966 --> 00:17:47,601
Jotaro: Avdol,
how you been doing?

361
00:17:47,634 --> 00:17:49,269
Kakyoin: It’s been a while.
How goes it?

362
00:17:49,303 --> 00:17:51,105
Joseph: So, avdol,
is the wound on your back

363
00:17:51,138 --> 00:17:52,706
- healing up all right?
- Avdol: It’s fine,

364
00:17:52,739 --> 00:17:54,741
though my joints do get
a little stiff sometimes.

365
00:17:54,775 --> 00:17:55,876
Polnareff: Hey!

366
00:17:55,909 --> 00:17:57,711
Jotaro: Has it
really been two weeks

367
00:17:57,744 --> 00:17:59,279
- since we last saw each other?
- Polnareff: Hey!

368
00:17:59,313 --> 00:18:01,248
Jotaro: We’re lucky
to all be alive.

369
00:18:01,281 --> 00:18:03,283
Avdol: Jotaro, you’re still
wearing your uniform?

370
00:18:03,317 --> 00:18:05,719
Don’t you ever get hot?
( Laughs )

371
00:18:05,752 --> 00:18:08,255
Polnareff: Hey,
just hold on a second, guys!

372
00:18:08,288 --> 00:18:09,689
( Groans )

373
00:18:09,723 --> 00:18:11,291
Didn’t you hear me?!

374
00:18:11,325 --> 00:18:13,661
I told you to hold on a second,
you assholes!

375
00:18:13,694 --> 00:18:16,597
What’s the deal with
those laissez-faire attitudes?!

376
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:19,099
A man we thought was dead
just waltzed onto the beach!

377
00:18:19,132 --> 00:18:21,167
How the hell
can you just brush it off

378
00:18:21,201 --> 00:18:22,803
and act like
nothing has changed?!

379
00:18:22,836 --> 00:18:25,072
Joseph: Oh, yeah.
I’m sorry about that, polnareff.

380
00:18:25,105 --> 00:18:27,808
When I told you
i’d taken it upon myself

381
00:18:27,841 --> 00:18:29,776
to Bury avdol in India,

382
00:18:29,810 --> 00:18:31,712
I may have lied.

383
00:18:31,745 --> 00:18:34,314
Polnareff: Wh-wh-what the hell?!

384
00:18:34,348 --> 00:18:37,051
Avdol: Mr. Joestar and jotaro
were the ones

385
00:18:37,084 --> 00:18:39,286
who tended to the wounds
on my head back in India

386
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:40,921
after I was shot by hol horse.

387
00:18:40,954 --> 00:18:42,789
( Polnareff sputters )

388
00:18:42,823 --> 00:18:46,727
You assholes have known avdol
was alive the entire time,

389
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:49,062
and never once did it cross
any of your deceitful minds

390
00:18:49,096 --> 00:18:50,264
to let me know?!

391
00:18:50,297 --> 00:18:52,266
I’m most surprised
at you, kakyoin!

392
00:18:52,299 --> 00:18:54,935
Kakyoin: I only found out
the day after it all happened.

393
00:18:54,968 --> 00:18:57,170
But it was imperative
to not let the enemy know,

394
00:18:57,204 --> 00:18:59,640
and since you have
such a big mouth, I suggested--

395
00:18:59,673 --> 00:19:01,108
pardon. What I meant to say

396
00:19:01,141 --> 00:19:03,744
was since it’s not easy
for you to lie on command,

397
00:19:03,777 --> 00:19:05,679
I suggested
we keep it a secret from you.

398
00:19:05,712 --> 00:19:06,913
( Polnareff gasps )

399
00:19:06,947 --> 00:19:09,216
Jotaro: If you’d
let the secret slip,

400
00:19:09,249 --> 00:19:12,185
avdol wouldn’t have been
able to recuperate in peace.

401
00:19:12,219 --> 00:19:14,054
Kakyoin: We were
planning to let you know

402
00:19:14,087 --> 00:19:16,022
the very moment
we knew that he was safe,

403
00:19:16,056 --> 00:19:18,325
but we didn’t think
you’d run into him first.

404
00:19:18,358 --> 00:19:20,660
Polnareff: Oh, yeah.
Avdol, we found your dad

405
00:19:20,694 --> 00:19:22,296
living in a hut on this island!

406
00:19:22,329 --> 00:19:24,031
Come on.
Let’s let him know you’re here!

407
00:19:24,064 --> 00:19:26,333
Avdol: Oh, that was
just me in disguise.

408
00:19:28,202 --> 00:19:30,438
Polnareff: Say what?!

409
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:33,673
Then you were in on it
from the very start?

410
00:19:33,707 --> 00:19:36,009
Everything that happened
was a ruse you created?

411
00:19:36,043 --> 00:19:38,345
Avdol: Don’t talk to me!
No one ever comes to visit

412
00:19:38,378 --> 00:19:40,413
when they have
good news to report!

413
00:19:40,447 --> 00:19:41,915
Just shut up!

414
00:19:42,983 --> 00:19:44,117
Joseph: Don’t go there.

415
00:19:44,151 --> 00:19:45,786
Avdol’s death wasn’t your fault.

416
00:19:45,819 --> 00:19:47,754
Polnareff: You didn’t
have to go that far!

417
00:19:47,788 --> 00:19:49,857
How dare you leave me
out of the loop?!

418
00:19:49,890 --> 00:19:52,259
I think that’s the cruelest
thing you’ve ever done to me!

419
00:19:52,292 --> 00:19:54,127
Joseph: Now, now, chin up.

420
00:19:54,161 --> 00:19:55,429
There’s no reason
for you to cry.

421
00:19:55,462 --> 00:19:57,164
Kakyoin: I’m sorry, polnareff.

422
00:19:57,197 --> 00:19:59,299
I truly didn’t think
you’d be this hurt.

423
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:02,002
- ( Jotaro growls )
- Avdol: I apologize as well,

424
00:20:02,035 --> 00:20:03,403
but I had a very good reason

425
00:20:03,437 --> 00:20:05,072
for coming to this island
in disguise.

426
00:20:05,105 --> 00:20:06,807
Polnareff: Yeah? What is it?

427
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:09,209
Joseph: It was partially
so the enemy wouldn’t find out,

428
00:20:09,243 --> 00:20:11,912
but I also had avdol
do some shopping for me

429
00:20:11,945 --> 00:20:13,146
while he was laying low.

430
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:15,082
Polnareff:
What kind of shopping?

431
00:20:15,115 --> 00:20:17,517
Avdol: Since it was
a very conspicuous acquisition,

432
00:20:17,551 --> 00:20:21,155
I disguised myself
as a wealthy arab gentlemen.

433
00:20:21,188 --> 00:20:24,825
Joseph: All right, everyone,
let’s climb aboard and head out!

434
00:20:24,858 --> 00:20:26,293
Come on, polnareff.

435
00:20:26,326 --> 00:20:28,094
For the love
of everything that’s sacred,

436
00:20:28,128 --> 00:20:29,796
- cheer up already.
- Polnareff: Huh?

437
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:31,465
Joseph: It’s almost here. Look.

438
00:20:31,498 --> 00:20:33,333
Polnareff: I don’t understand.
What’s almost here?

439
00:20:33,367 --> 00:20:35,803
I don’t see anything! ( Gasps )

440
00:20:35,836 --> 00:20:37,471
♪

441
00:20:37,504 --> 00:20:39,473
What?!

442
00:20:43,977 --> 00:20:46,813
Whoa! A submarine?!

443
00:20:46,847 --> 00:20:48,315
Joseph: That’s right.

444
00:20:48,348 --> 00:20:51,418
From here on out,
we’re riding to Egypt in this.

445
00:20:51,451 --> 00:20:53,453
Polnareff:
Y-you’ve gotta be kidding!

446
00:20:53,487 --> 00:20:55,222
How did you afford this?!

447
00:21:00,427 --> 00:21:02,429
♪

448
00:21:14,308 --> 00:21:16,577
♪ All the old paintings
on the tomb ♪

449
00:21:16,610 --> 00:21:19,046
♪ they do the sand dance,
don’t you know ♪

450
00:21:19,079 --> 00:21:20,180
♪ if they move too quick

451
00:21:20,214 --> 00:21:21,549
♪ oh, whey, oh

452
00:21:21,582 --> 00:21:23,517
♪ they’re falling down
like a domino ♪

453
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:26,053
♪ all the bazaar men
by the nile ♪

454
00:21:26,086 --> 00:21:28,155
♪ they got the money on a bet

455
00:21:28,188 --> 00:21:29,356
♪ gold crocodiles

456
00:21:29,389 --> 00:21:30,891
♪ oh, whey, oh

457
00:21:30,924 --> 00:21:32,959
♪ they snap their teeth
on your cigarette ♪

458
00:21:32,993 --> 00:21:35,128
♪ foreign types
with the hookah pipes say ♪

459
